## Superseded standard pin (T5.3, 2026-05-18)

This archive resolved **Q-004** (Workiva fabricated symbols, 2026-05-11)
by realigning `.forge/standards/flutter/opentelemetry.md` from v1.0.0
to v1.1.0 on the actual Workiva `opentelemetry 0.18.11` API surface
(9 fabricated symbols removed, 7 verified added).

The v1.1.0 standard has been **superseded** by v2.0.0 in T5.3
(`t5-otel-dartastic-realign`, archived 2026-05-18) due to **Q-006** —
Workiva's web-only platform mismatch (discovered 2026-05-16 via
`cli-trust-harness` Option B validation, post-this-archive). Q-004
fixed Axis 2 (API surface) ; Q-006 exposed the missing Axis 3
(platform compatibility) which Q-004's procedure had not checked.

The substitution moves to the Dartastic ecosystem :

- `dartastic_opentelemetry_api: ^1.0.0-beta.2` (transitive, WAIVER
  per ADR-T53-002)
- `dartastic_opentelemetry: ^1.1.0-beta.6`
- `flutterrific_opentelemetry: ^0.4.0`

All 3 packages declare support for all 6 Flutter platforms (Android,
iOS, Linux, macOS, Web, Windows) — the 3-axis checklist from T5.2
(`t5-2-platform-verification`, archived 2026-05-18) was applied
inline in T5.3's `proposal.md` § Source Documents, and embedded in
the v2.0.0 standard itself.

